Passcode: 219002

---

Hi WeThinkCode_ student cohort of 2020,

As you may know, we're hosting our first round of expert-led workshops. Please note that attendance is compulsory.

By this stage, you've already had some exposure to the concept and practice of unit testing through your coding problems.

In the workshop, we'll be introducing the powerful practice of Test Driven Development (TDD), which is a tremendously useful approach and skill to have a software a developer. It will serve you well in your careers (and perhaps even in life).

Workshop Preparation & Registration

Please complete the following set up BEFORE the workshop on the computer you will be using to attend. We will not have any time to deal with technical issues during the session so you will not able to participate if you don't do this.

Requirements

You should already have these if you're working on campus machines (WTC_ OS).

  • Zoom Desktop Client (not browser)
  • Visual Studio Code
  • Git
  • Bash shell
  • Python3 with the venv package installed

Instructions

  1. Download the workshop materials here

  2. Unzip it to your home directory and run setup.sh(instructions also in REAMDE.md).

  3. NB Enter your WTC_ student email address

  4. NB Enter the workshop key: tdd-h

  5. Confirm that the setup.sh completes successfully.

  6. Test your Zoom desktop client and be sure to use a username that we can refer to you by (not your youtube/twitch handle)

Please open a Zendesk ticket if you're unable to complete these steps.

Join from a PC, Mac, iPad, iPhone or Android device:

---

Hi WeThinkCode_ student cohort of 2020,

As you may know, we're hosting our first round of expert-led workshops. Please note that attendance is compulsory.

By this stage, you've already had some exposure to the concept and practice of unit testing through your coding problems.

In the workshop, we'll be introducing the powerful practice of Test Driven Development (TDD), which is a tremendously useful approach and skill to have a software a developer. It will serve you well in your careers (and perhaps even in life).

Workshop Preparation & Registration

Please complete the following set up BEFORE the workshop on the computer you will be using to attend. We will not have any time to deal with technical issues during the session so you will not able to participate if you don't do this.

Requirements

You should already have these if you're working on campus machines (WTC_ OS).

  • Zoom Desktop Client (not browser)
  • Visual Studio Code
  • Git
  • Bash shell
  • Python3 with the venv package installed

Instructions

  1. Download the workshop materials here

  2. Unzip it to your home directory and run setup.sh(instructions also in REAMDE.md).

  3. NB Enter your WTC_ student email address

  4. NB Enter the workshop key: tdd-h

  5. Confirm that the setup.sh completes successfully.

  6. Test your Zoom desktop client and be sure to use a username that we can refer to you by (not your youtube/twitch handle)

Please open a Zendesk ticket if you're unable to complete these steps.

Join from a PC, Mac, iPad, iPhone or Android device:
